# NSW Rental Bond Explorer

Single-page data explorer for NSW rental bond lodgement data, built with React, TypeScript, Vite, and Tailwind CSS v4.

## Tech stack

- **Runtime**: React 19 + TypeScript 5.9
- **Build**: Vite 6 with `@vitejs/plugin-react`
- **Styling**: Tailwind CSS 4.2 via `@tailwindcss/vite` plugin (no `tailwind.config.js` — v4 uses CSS-based config)
- **Package manager**: pnpm 9.12

No routing library, no state management library, no component library. All UI components are built from scratch.

## File structure

```
src/
  main.tsx                    # React entry point (renders <App />)
  App.tsx                     # Top-level orchestrator (~460 lines) — state, useMemo chains, layout
  App.css                     # @import "tailwindcss" + minimal custom CSS
  types.ts                    # TypeScript interfaces and constants
  utils.ts                    # Pure helper functions, constants, data transforms
  hooks/
    useRentalData.ts          # Data loading, month switching, XLSX download
  components/
    Charts.tsx                # HistogramChart, BubbleMatrix (Recharts-based)
    DataTable.tsx             # Sortable table with pagination
    FilterPanel.tsx           # Collapsible filter panel (composes MultiSelect, TagInput, RangeSlider)
    StatsPanel.tsx            # Min / Avg / Max summary cards
    MultiSelect.tsx           # Custom dropdown with checkboxes
    TagInput.tsx              # Text input that converts values into removable tag pills
    RangeSlider.tsx           # Dual-handle range slider
    ThemeDropdown.tsx         # Light / Dark / System theme picker
  __tests__/                  # Vitest unit tests for components and utils
e2e/
  app.spec.ts                 # Playwright E2E tests
public/
  rental-bonds-*.json         # Dataset per month (~30k records each, ~3 MB)
index.html                    # HTML shell
vite.config.js                # Vite + React + Tailwind plugins
playwright.config.ts          # Playwright config (auto-starts dev server)
```

## Data source

NSW Fair Trading Rental Bond Lodgements, one XLSX file per month converted to JSON. Each record has: `lodgementDate` (string), `postcode` (number), `dwellingType` (string: F/H/T/O/R/U), `bedrooms` (number | null), `weeklyRent` (number). Loaded via `fetch` on mount; the available months are discovered from a manifest in production or probed via HEAD in dev.

## Architecture

**App.tsx** is the orchestrator: it owns filter/sort/group/page/theme state, computes derived data via `useMemo` chains (`filtered` -> `sorted` -> `grouped`, plus `stats`, `chartBins`, `hasActiveFilters`, `filterSummary`), and composes the extracted components.

**useRentalData hook** encapsulates data lifecycle: init loading, month discovery, month switching, and XLSX download/parse.

**Components** are presentational with props-based APIs:

- **FilterPanel** — collapsible panel composing MultiSelect, TagInput, RangeSlider
- **DataTable** — sortable table with pagination controls
- **StatsPanel** — min/avg/max summary cards
- **Charts** — HistogramChart (line chart) and BubbleMatrix (scatter chart) using Recharts
- **MultiSelect** — custom dropdown with checkboxes; outside-click-to-close via `useRef` + `mousedown`
- **TagInput** — text input converting typed values into removable tag pills on Enter/comma
- **RangeSlider** — dual-handle range slider using two overlaid `<input type="range">` elements
- **ThemeDropdown** — light/dark/system theme picker with outside-click-to-close

## Styling approach

- ~95% Tailwind utility classes inline in JSX
- `src/App.css` contains only `@import "tailwindcss"` plus custom CSS for things Tailwind cannot express: range slider vendor pseudo-elements (`::-webkit-slider-thumb`), spinner keyframe animation, collapse open/closed states, multi-select compound selectors
- Color palette uses Tailwind defaults: indigo-600 as accent, gray-50/100/200/500/700/900 for neutrals
- Panels use `bg-gray-50 border border-gray-200 rounded-xl shadow-sm`; dashboard tiles use `bg-indigo-50 border border-indigo-100`; table header is `bg-indigo-50`; table rows are zebra-striped

## Dev server notes

- Vite HMR does **not** work with this Google Drive-synced workspace path. After code changes, kill and restart the dev server.
- Use `pnpm cleanup` to kill any stale Vite processes on ports 5173–5178, then `pnpm dev` to start fresh.

## Conventions

- No external component or UI libraries — build custom components
- Each component lives in its own file under `src/components/`; hooks under `src/hooks/`
- `App.tsx` is the orchestrator — state management and layout composition only
- Use Tailwind utility classes for styling; only add custom CSS in `App.css` when Tailwind cannot express it (vendor pseudo-elements, keyframe animations, compound state selectors)
- Types and constants go in `src/types.ts`; pure functions and shared constants go in `src/utils.ts`
